The paper deals with the problem of mapping logical qubits to physical qubits in quantum computing, which is a fundamental problem in the field of quantum computing. This problem is related to the design and optimization of algorithms and compilers for quantum computers, which falls under the category of computer science. The paper proposes a heuristic search algorithm for solving this problem, which involves optimization techniques and data structures, making it relevant to the sub-categories of cs.ET (Emerging Technologies), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.PL (Programming Languages), and cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
